            . I am a <rs id="t18321018-37-viclabel218" type="occupation">shoemaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18321018-37-victim452 t18321018-37-viclabel218"></join>, and live at <placeName id="t18321018-37-crimeloc219">Battle-bridge</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18321018-37-crimeloc219" type="placeName" value="Battle-bridge"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18321018-37-crimeloc219" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18321018-37-off216 t18321018-37-crimeloc219"></join>. On the 26th of September I was standing in the shop, about half-past twelve o'clock in the morning; I saw the two prisoners, who I suspected - I watched them some time, and then went into the parlour; I looked through the blind - one of them came to the sill of the door, lifted up a pair of boots, and then let them down again; I then saw Simmons come and take them -Oliver was close to him, and another person was with them<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183210180033"></xptr>- they walked away: I pursued, and took them next door - Oliver then had the boots in his apron; these are them.</p>
               <p>Oliver's Defence. Another boy took them, and ran away.</p>
               <p>Simmons' Defence. Another boy took them, who had no shoes on - he threw them to Oliver's feet, and he took them up.</p>
               <p>OLIVER - <rs id="t18321018-37-verdict220" type="verdictDescription">
